properties.areaDesc: Delaware Bay waters north of East Point NJ to Slaughter Beach DE
properties.headline: Gale Warning issued January 7 at 12:36PM EST until January 8 at 10:00PM EST by NWS Mount Holly NJ
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Gale Warning, west winds 15 to 25 kt with gusts
up to 40 kt and very rough waters expected. For the Small
Craft Advisory, northwest winds 10 to 20 kt with gusts up to
25 kt and choppy waters expected.

* WHERE...Delaware Bay waters north of East Point NJ to
Slaughter Beach DE.

* WHEN...For the Gale Warning, from 6 AM to 10 PM EST Wednesday.
For the Small Craft Advisory, from 6 PM this evening to 6 AM
EST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Low pressure intensifying offshore will
lead to quickly changing conditions late this evening. There
will be an improvement in conditions overnight before gale force
winds develop on Wednesday.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 6 PM THIS EVENING TO 6 AM EST WEDNESDAY... ...GALE WARNING NOW IN EFFECT FROM 6 AM TO 10 PM EST WEDNESDAY
